On my Dad's 79th birthday, I think of my father's legacy... family, faith, hard work, money smarts, and creating opportunities. What is your legacy⁉️🤔⁣
⁣
Those 5 things I came up with makes me think of my own story as a person and as a father.  What will my kids say about me whenever they finally are out there in person or on social media? 🥰⁣
⁣
My Dad, Mohammad Umar, has always sought opportunity, which I find the most inspiring. ✅⁣
⁣
He left Pakistan to study abroad in the UK. He was the first among his siblings to leave the roost on his own by himself. Though technically his older sister was in the UK after her marriage. ⁣
⁣
He was the first to come to Canada and start a brand new life. In the beginning it was just him, my mom, my older sister and brother. I showed up just 3 months later. Another brother showed up. ⁣
⁣
Soon, he created opportunity by sponsoring and supporting our extended family to come here. We built a pretty small but vibrant community on the East Coast, in New Brunswick.⁣
⁣
Opportunity came again as he quit his 20+ year career, moved a thousand miles away to Toronto, to start an entrepreneurial journey in business and tax accounting. ⁣
⁣
I could talk about all the other 4 aspects mentioned above. But opportunity is the one that strikes me today.⁣
⁣
Imagine Dad... if you didn't seek out opportunity or create it for yourself. Where would that stagnation or hesitation leave you? Gosh, where would I be? I'm so grateful for the life I have, the family and friends, and more. 🙏🏾⁣
⁣
HAPPY 79th BIRTHDAY DAD‼️ Thank you for the story, legacy and example you are leading. May you continue to stay healthy, vibrant, and make more memories with our ever expanding family. ❤️⁣
⁣
What are the FIVE things you want to be remembered for? I'd love to hear your thoughts. 👇🏾⁣
⁣
For me personally, I hope my kids see my heart, my affection, and maybe my nerd-like passions, haha. 🤓⁣
⁣
I'm off to to dinner with Dad and the rest... ⁣
⁣
#PowerOfConnection #Family #Gratitude #Birthday #Dads #birthdaywishes #fathers #fatherandson

My marriage hit 21 years today, yet could’ve ended 4 years in. But it's not what you think...⁣
⁣
You see, my wife, life partner & best friend in 2006 went into septic shock, the emergency room was frantically trying to keep her alive. ⁣
⁣
I stood there, watching the commotion, hardly believing what was going on. But the sounds & sights were clear
⁣
The sound of 6 doctors, nurses and technicians yelling at each other working together, the beeps of numerous instruments, the blur of someone talking in my ear - I'm not taking in a word.⁣
⁣
The sight of her bed surrounded while the other patients waited, the heart rate line zig zagging along w/ other rapidly changing numbers on the machines, tubes & blood, & I remember a lot of bright lights.⁣
⁣
I just felt helpless. ⁣
⁣
Thankfully an amazing cardiologist pulled strings, brought in tons of ppl to test, analyze, finally figure out what happened. It was E coli. Ananda stayed in the ICU for a week and in the hospital another week. Dr. M & the team saved her life.⁣

We’d started our life together. 2 mths earlier I left the corp world. We wanted kids, but life got in the way. That year we sorted was important to us, what kind of life to live.⁣

You brought back my best friend, my laugh track, my hug machine, my advisor & moral compass. 🥰⁣
⁣
We brought into the world two beautiful children, Nyal and Ryah. who are smart, charming, & talented. 😍⁣
⁣
We've had our ups and downs, that's how marriage works. All of it is rooted in values of love, kindness, empathy and compassion. 💜⁣
⁣
But there was no scarier moment for me when in that emergency room, thinking of my life, w/ a wife or w/o a wife. ⁣

Are your LinkedIn views or engagement going down⁉️ Short answer is yes, but the big question is do you need to worry❓🤔👇🏾⁣
⁣
Personally, I have seen about a 60% to 70% drop engagement from my content over the past 3 to 4 weeks. Yeah that’s right! I’m a numbers nerd. 🤓⁣
⁣
And many of my other LinkedIn content creator friends have said the same.⁣
⁣
Engagement on that platform is always changing. When videos first came out we were getting tons of views on then then it got lower. And now it’s much lower. The same goes for most types of content. The same thing happens on other digital platforms too. That’s okay. ⁣
⁣
❇️ MY ADVICE: continue to share content, start conversations, engage folks on the platform and keep showing off your expertise and building a strong thought leadership personal brand. You got to play the long game and it will yield results. 💯⁣
⁣
That said, my MAIN concern is the lack of transparency around who signs up to see our content and who does Linkedin show it to?  Here are three key areas.⁣
⁣
1️⃣ BELL RINGERS: while I don’t know the actual number of people who ring my bell to get notified of my posts, I do know there’s enough of them that when I do post, I often get 20-30 people who engage. But lately it’s less than 5.⁣
⁣
2️⃣ NEWSLETTER SUBSCRIBERS: I have almost 13,000 subscribers but yet when I post a newsletter now, the engagement is less than 50, or 0.4%. In fact, I’ve signed up for several newsletters, and many times I don’t see when they publish.⁣
⁣
3️⃣ COMPANY PAGE FOLLOWERS: I have 22,500 followers on my best page. Yet whenever I post the average engagement is zero likes and 5-25 “impressions” or 0.02% - 0.1%. ⁣
⁣
That’s deeply concerning to me. Linkedin users sign up in good faith to get content, but LinkedIn won’t give it to them. So we need to keep advocating and pushing LI to be more transparent and the show our audience the content they signed up for. ✊🏾⁣
⁣
What do you think? (Gosh will people even see that post? Hope so!) Just to be safe, I’ll post it here. 🔥🙏⁣

Every year, do you reflect, set goals and make plans and priorities… with your kids⁉️😲👇🏾⁣
⁣
You'll be surprised by the results and benefit of this. The other day we spoke to Nyal. 😍⁣
⁣
We started this when the kids were 12. It honestly began in desperation as we sought advice from parenting experts from our kid's challenges during the pandemic. 🥰⁣
⁣
Now we take Ryah and then Nyal each out for an annual check-in. Each kid is different, so you need to keep that in mind. Here's how you can do it too. ⁣
⁣
You let them talk about and reflect on the last year. It takes longer than you think and lots of patience. But our kids, much like my business which is a third baby, are worth it. 💯⁣
⁣
You look at and listen to new ambitions, share challenges and concerns that they have, and anything parents and teachers have observed. 🤓⁣
⁣
You then determine how you can best support them as parents. After that you put together a plan you all agree on. ✅⁣
⁣
And no Nyal is still not getting a smartphone, LOL. But he knows why. A recent study showed the harmful effects. ⁣
⁣
Still not convinced about doing this? Well we DID also find out some interesting things they want to do…⁣
⁣
🟢 Nyal wants to better at small talk, start a YouTube channel and get a sub 10-second Rubik’s cube solve. ⁣
⁣
🟣 Ryah wants to get back into acting, maybe get on a TV show, workout with her mom, and plan more friend events.⁣
⁣
And of course one BONUS TIP is to help guide the conversation for them based on talking about “Personal Responsibilities” to:⁣
 ⁣

2️⃣ Learning & Growth⁣

What does fatherhood mean to you⁉️ ⁣

2️⃣ My kids and my journey with them ⁣
3️⃣ Other fatherly role models I appreciate and learn from ⁣

🟢 My Dad Mohammad Umar is all about an incredibly hard work ethic, doing everything you can to support the kids and family financially, and the lesson of “there is no tomorrow” which has many meanings for me. ⁣
⁣
🟣 My kids Nyal and Ryah teach me patience, fun, empathy, challenging my own ideas and beliefs, making every moment count and be a role model. Most of all I’ve felt my heart bursting with love 100x over in a way that I could never ever explain. 😍⁣
⁣
🟠 Other dads teach me best practices,  how to innovate, and lastly to learn that I’m not alone with the struggles and guilt of screwing up sometimes. ⁣
⁣
🟡 But role models include mothers, older siblings, and mentors. If you look hard enough and listen carefully, there is a wealth of love, learning and support around you to give you greater purpose.⁣
⁣
🔴 Finally my father-in-law Bob Dobbs, who passed away 7 years ago, was another role model on loving your family with all your might, doing acts of service to show that love, and I miss having his calm rational thoughts on the topics of the day. ⁣

Happy Father’s Day‼️ I feel blessed. 🙏🥰⁣

THREADS is here‼️ Follow me on Meta's new competitor to Twitter. As a huge Twitter user (506k followers) here's my take. 🤓👇🏾⁣
⁣
Instagram Threads is a HUGE threat to Twitter, despite several other startup apps, for many reasons:⁣
⁣
1️⃣ Meta and Mark Zuckerberg have a ton of resources at their disposal⁣
⁣
2️⃣ Meta has a very strong existing user base to leverage, which means it can grow quickly. 50 million users in 24 hours! (I was number 6.35 million)⁣
⁣
3️⃣ Twitter is still in chaos. The schoolyard has been taken over by a bully who bought out the entire district. Until they create more stability, Twitter is going to struggle. Breaking news is they just launched a lawsuit against Threads. ⁣
⁣
𝐓𝐇𝐑𝐄𝐀𝐃𝐒 𝐁𝐀𝐒𝐈𝐂 𝐎𝐕𝐄𝐑𝐕𝐈𝐄𝐖⁣

⁣
🔵 Can upload videos, images, and more, just not Gifs. I love that videos can be 5 min long vs. 2:20 for Twitter⁣
⁣
🟢 Just like IG it’s mostly focused on the mobile experience, so keep that in mind for portrait/square videos and photos⁣
⁣
🔴 Still missing a ton of things like editable posts, auto-captions, no DMs, no hashtags.⁣
⁣

That doesn't mean these apps can't co-exist. I mean look at the current digital layout.⁣

3️⃣ COMMUNITY MATTERS: Given her large friend circle, the family circle, and her communities amongst fellow Muslims, Pakistanis, and South Asians, Ammi has relied on them and supported them. ⁣
⁣
4️⃣ WORK HARD & NURTURE: If there is one thing both my parents are guilty of, it's working too hard. But the lessons to go above and beyond, to nurture and nourish (her cooking is fantastic!), to create real impact with your effort, are timeless.⁣

5️⃣ DO WHAT IT TAKES: Decades ago, my mom worked in a factory on an assembly line wiring hair dryers, electric fans and more. ⁣
His legacy. 👇🏾⁣
